# Licensing Requirements

## License Selection
- Every project must have an explicitly chosen license
- License must be compatible with all project dependencies
- License must be approved by the organization
- License selection must be documented

## Required Files
- LICENSE file in project root
- License field in package.json (JS/TS projects)
- License documentation in README.md
- License compatibility analysis in documentation

## Validation
- CI/CD must validate license compatibility
- Dependencies must be checked for license conflicts
- License must be properly formatted
- License year and copyright holder must be correct

## Documentation
- README must include:
  - License name and version
  - Brief license description
  - Any additional terms or conditions
  - Instructions for compliance
- Documentation must be kept up to date with any license changes